<br>
Sometimes you meet jerks who get their name written on my special lucky notepad of morons, and sometimes I get to find new people to add ot my /friends list. <br>
<br>
If I choose to not be guilded for whatever reason I like, why should the game become stale and dead to me based on that decision? Why should this one choice lock me down to 2 zones for all realistic intents and purposes?<br>
<br>
I may still squirm my way into BoT. A good friend saw my venting here and has offered to help me out next time they are doing a run for key pieces.<br>
<br>
But why should it take a pity leg-up for me to be able to do so? A game that for 3 years has entertained and in fact flourished based on the sheer size of the world and its opportunities should not suddenly be compressed into a few measly zones just because I take the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>option</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - and its my option damnit! Guilding is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>not</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mandatory! - just as I rise to the pinnacle of my power? <p><center>
