<br>
I myself like to spend time with a couple of guildies in non-pop zones. Trashing through seb, killing nameds in UP, trying solo kills you've never thought possible etc.<br>
If you want exp, go to PoV, farm for a couple of hours and you have more aa's then some months ago in a week of Frenzy / Juggs. Then when you get bored with out, go out and do fun stuff again.<br>
<br>
I am trying to do the quest for the HoH key. It requires killing Agony Mephits in PoN. I've only done goblins thereso far, but trying to find the entrance to the mephit cave and running into 2 named goblins that kept summoning people was more fun then the 2 nights before when I'd done about 8 aa.<br>
<br>
Go out and have fun, do things that seem hard (solo Phinny or a Dragon) or just plain fun. Do quests, get a tradeskill up.<br>
<br>
Now that I don't worry about exp anymore my life has only improved a lot with PoP. If I think I need some more AA's I go to PoV and spend a couple of days there. That's no more fun then soloing FG, doing UD/Frenzy in velks or farm lame stuff in Seb which was the general way to spend your time before pop. <br>
Want exp? get some at the designated exp zones, want fun? ignore exp altogether and have FUN.<br>
<br>
